tcpdump - command-line packet analyzer
Source: https://www.tcpdump.org/

Usage:
tcpdump -i <interface> -s <number> -w <file.pcap>

Options:
-i    interface
-s    number of packets to intercept
-w    output filename.pcap
-n    disable DNS resolution

Informational:
https://packettotal.com - this tool will analyze .pcap file for you and report for sus activity
